    • Method Detail

      • selectByClick

        DOMWindow selectByClick(int index)
        Simulates a real selection event (click on the select and clik on the option). It is a shortcut for clicking on this element and then on the option to select. It waits until the document at the new location (if any), is fully loaded. If the event triggers opening a new window, it is returned as result, otherwise the current window is returned
        Parameters:
        index - the index position
        Returns:
        If a window has been opened due to the event, the new window is returned, otherwise the current window is returned (which may have a new location).

      • selectByClick

        DOMWindow selectByClick(String optiontext)
        Simulates a real selection event (click on the select and clik on the option). It is a shortcut for clicking on this element and then on the option to select. It waits until the document at the new location (if any), is fully loaded. If the event triggers opening a new window, it is returned as result, otherwise the current window is returned
        Parameters:
        index - the option displayed text
        Returns:
        If a window has been opened due to the event, the new window is returned, otherwise the current window is returned (which may have a new location).

      • getType

        String getType()
        Returns:
